{
  "stem": "13395.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There-- they put their old grandparents on the buggies, covered them with-- with blankets, tied the goats to the buggies, and schlepped them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was an exodus of people, and it was such a sad picture to see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were leaving.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They didn't know where they're going, but they're running away from the border, because they thought that this is where the fight-- that that's where the war is going to be.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they left everything behind, just took some food and clothing and some animals with them, and just left towards Poland, inside Poland.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "My grandmother phoned up that she's leaving, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I remember my mother said, stay where you are.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Don't go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It's too late to go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I know the German strength.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I saw what was happening in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I know that the Poles have not gotten a chance.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And you'll see that, in no time, Germany will overrun all of Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But she wanted to-- us to be safe, so she sent my sister and myself to some friends, which I don't even know-- I didn't even know her name, their names.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "She gave us the address.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We got on the bicycle-- it was about 30 kilometers from our town-- and we put on our Girl Guide uniform-- till this day I don't understand why-- and we went, showing, probably, the-- our allegiance to Poland.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I have no idea what made us do this, but we were lucky that we weren't killed because of that, because when the Nazis marched into Katowice, which was 20 kilometers from us, a Girl Guide in her uniform approached a German officer, presented him with flowers, welcomed him to Poland, and shot him.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they were looking for everyone that was in that organization.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
